## Allow Build/sync on PUBLISHED domains + fix Settings lockdown (issue #78)

### Context

GitHub issue #78 (reported by @ulsmo) identified two problems introduced when
the domain lifecycle (DRAFT / IN-REVIEW / PUBLISHED) was added in v0.5.0:

1. The Knowledge Graph **Build** button is disabled on PUBLISHED/IN-REVIEW
   domains. Because the build/sync operations only re-materialise triples from
   source data using the frozen design (they do not change the design), this
   restriction was too broad: a published domain's graph cannot be refreshed
   without reverting to DRAFT, which defeats the purpose of publishing for
   production consumption.

2. The **Settings** page fields (warehouse, Lakebase engine, base URI, etc.)
   are wrongly greyed out when a PUBLISHED domain is loaded. These are
   application-global settings entirely independent of any domain's lifecycle
   status; they were never server-side status-gated.

### Changes

1. `src/shared/fastapi/main.py`
   - Removed `/dtwin/sync/start`, `/dtwin/sync/load`, and
     `/dtwin/reasoning/materialize` from `_STATUS_GATE_EDIT_PATHS`. These
     data-refresh endpoints are now status-open; they remain builder-role-gated
     via their endpoint decorators.
   - Updated the lifecycle gate comments to document the design/data split.

2. `src/front/static/global/css/permissions.css`
   - Deleted the `read-only-status` build-button gate (the block that disabled
     `#syncStartBtn` and `[data-sync-action="start-triple-store-sync"]` on
     non-DRAFT versions).
   - Added `:not([data-page="settings"])` to each of the three generic
     form-field read-only selectors, alongside the existing
     `:not([data-page="digitaltwin"])` exclusion.
   - Updated the comment block to document both the `digitaltwin` and
     `settings` page-level exclusions.

3. `src/front/static/global/js/version-check.js`
   - Removed `document.body.classList.add('read-only-status')` (now dead after
     the CSS gate removal).
   - Updated comments to clarify that build/sync/materialise are data-refresh
     ops and are not gated on lifecycle status.

4. `src/front/templates/settings.html`
   - Added `{% block page_id %}settings{% endblock %}` so `<body>` carries
     `data-page="settings"`, making the CSS page-level exclusion effective.

5. `tests/units/auth/test_permission_middleware.py`
   - Added `TestDataRefreshNotStatusGated`: asserts that a builder on a
     PUBLISHED/IN-REVIEW version can reach `/dtwin/sync/start`,
     `/dtwin/sync/load`, `/dtwin/reasoning/materialize`, while design-editing
     paths (`/ontology/`) remain blocked, and viewers remain role-blocked
     regardless of status.

6. `tests/units/api/test_ui_rendering.py`
   - Added `test_body_has_page_id_settings` to `TestSettingsPage`: asserts
     `data-page="settings"` is present in the rendered `/settings` page body.

